THE HOUSEMAID is a wildly entertaining thriller starring Sydney Sweeney and Amanda Seyfried, based on the best-selling book. From director Paul Feig, the film plunges audiences into a twisted world where perfection is an illusion, and nothing is as it seems. Trying to escape her past, Millie (Sweeney) accepts a job as a live-in housemaid for the wealthy Nina (Seyfried) and Andrew Winchester (Brandon Sklenar). But what begins as a dream job quickly unravels into something far more dangerous ‚Äì a sexy, seductive game of secrets, scandal, and power. Behind the Winchesters‚Äô closed doors lies a world of shocking twists that will leave you guessing until the very end.

snippet.title: "Put Up Some Fences" - Marsh Family parody of "Walking in Memphis" about Donald Trump UK State Visit
snippet.description:
‚ÄúWalking in Memphis‚Äù was first written and released by Marc Cohn in 1991, a heartfelt soul-filled, gospel-inflected autobiographical ballad about his journey as a struggling musician, in a 1985 trip from New York to Tennessee to find artistic inspiration. We‚Äôve always loved it ‚Äì it was our summer holiday playlist again this year ‚Äì and we‚Äôve used it to reflect on the trip that‚Äôs been all over the news in the UK, which is the official second state visit of Donald Trump. Sorry to those of you who pick out the shoddy Midi bagpipes in the audio mix ‚Äì but it wasn‚Äôt worth buying a proper sample for the little flourish ‚Ä¶ we‚Äôre sure the real ones will be much better at cutting through, and good at drowning out any painful conversations, at least for a few minutes.

For a full itinerary and summary/lowdown on Trump‚Äôs UK state visit, including some reflections on the protests, see: https://www.itv.com/news/2025-09-15/what-to-expect-as-us-president-makes-unprecedented-second-state-visit.

For information about the protests: https://www.standard.co.uk/news/london/stop-trump-coalition-march-donald-trump-state-visit-protest-london-b1247913.html.

For a bit of background of the furore with disgraced ambassador Peter Mandelson, see here: https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/articles/cx25xn2e8zqo.

___________________________

- PayPal to leave us a tip jar: https://paypal.me/marshfamilysongs 
- Patreon for ongoing support & bonuses: https://www.patreon.com/marshfamilysongs 

Find our other channels here: https://linktr.ee/marshfamilysongs 

Follow us here:

- https://bsky.app/profile/marshfamilysongs.bsky.social 
- https://open.spotify.com/artist/6AYmbCwi92V29y69lkRkRa 

___________________________

LYRICS:

The country‚Äôs not enthused
That Trump‚Äôs boarded a plane
Why brown-nose a man who just spreads abuse
When there‚Äôs little for us all to gain?
Delicately handled - the whole trip will have to be
Yeah, it‚Äôs like the worst state visit
You gotta feel for the monarchy!

So it won‚Äôt be contentious
They‚Äôll limit who Trump meets when he scoffs his meal
Stiff and pretentious
The royals won‚Äôt reveal the way we feel!

Fawning hosts with heralds
The troops lined up to view
Butter him up with some Kate and William
Keep him blocked from public view

Now security‚Äôs not the reason
Why he‚Äôs touring towers and tombs
But it‚Äôs a pretty shitty thing
Waiting for the king:
A clown in the royal rooms!

They‚Äôll have to put up some fences
Won‚Äôt be walking on the streets - keep protests concealed
Stuffed in a carriage
Be like some kind of Disneyland ordeal

They‚Äôve got napkins on the table
They‚Äôve got bagpipes in the air
And businessmen keen to get some deals through
Cos there‚Äôs tariffs everywhere
But, boy, this whole affair is senseless
 
Now it‚Äôs true Starmer‚Äôs chasing shadows
Every sign is that his polls aren‚Äôt good
And he thought his new ambassador
Was an asset that he understood
Turned out quite a bummer!
Mandelson was no white knight ‚Ä¶
Now he‚Äôs helped to ensure the Epstein files are
Back on the news tonight!
 
Why‚Äôd we allow this?
(Why‚Äôd we allow this?)
It‚Äôs hardly some great feat of diplomacy!
Offering a butt kiss
(Offering a butt kiss)
To a leech on world stability!

Damaging tariffs ‚Ä¶
(Damaging tariffs)
Here‚Äôs a meet-and-greet, to take the knee!
While proto-fascists
(While his proto-fascists)
Talk of overthrowing sovereignty

The country‚Äôs not enthused
That Trump‚Äôs boarded a plane
There‚Äôs taxes we spend that are put to use ‚Ä¶
And then others a pointless drain
There‚Äôs people whose actions deserve salutes
Hope he never gets to tour again
